le users and all works fine with sync clients. \r\nwhen we try to access files by the share link, we get *sometimes* a 404.\r\nthis only happens when we try to **share a file that was renamed and then shared via link**. we also found out that it does not help if we rename the file. \r\n\r\nhere are three experiments that we tried to narrow done the cause of the issue:\r\n## experiment 1: causes the bug\r\n1. upload a file via web interface (into a shared folder) \r\n2. rename the newly uploaded file\r\n3. share the file by link\r\n\r\nthis results in a 404.\r\n\r\n## experiment 2: without renaming\r\nthese steps lead to working link  (same directory, same user, same file) \r\n\r\n1. upload the file via web interface (again a shared folder)\r\n2. share file by link\r\n\r\nthis results in a working link.\r\n\r\n## experiment 3: in a not shared folder\r\nlast setup: like the first experiment but not within a shared folder\r\n\r\n1. upload a file via web interface (into a not shared folder)\r\n2. rename the uploaded file\r\n3. share file by link\r\n\r\nresult: all good, everything works as expected.\r\n\r\nwhat else do you need to reproduce this issue?\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"mtgap","id":1097106,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f52d29a66f285a1d61125dd69ac0766b2.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"454a73ee5feeb428d0c163a48903332c","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap","html_url":"https://github.com/mtgap","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mtgap/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.